genresAdvancedInfo.name: deep contemporary country
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Deep contemporary country is a subgenre of country music that embraces a more introspective and emotional approach. It often features slower tempos, acoustic instrumentation, and lyrics that explore themes of heartbreak, loss, and personal growth. Artists in this genre include Chris Stapleton, Kacey Musgraves, and Miranda Lambert.
